# Grace · the golden guidance of the Erdtree

Grace is the golden blessing of the Erdtree. It shows itself two ways at once: as the light in a Tarnished's eyes that marks the Erdtree's favor, and as the literal golden rays that gather at sites of lost grace, pointing the way forward. In play it is the game's compass, its checkpoint, and its resurrection rolled into one — to die and rise again at grace is the game's heartbeat.

The Tarnished were those whose grace was taken. Its return to them is the story's first mystery: the graceless, guided by gold once more, are drawn back to war for the Ring. Grace does not explain itself; it simply points, and the Tarnished follow.

It belongs to the frame because it is the structure the whole journey rests on — the thing that orients, preserves, and revives the player at every step. Its emergence is spiritual: grace is favor made visible, the Erdtree's blessing reaching into the eyes of those it marks and lighting the way they must walk.
